    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but small actions dont actually fix the mass extinctions or the heatwaves. it just feels like we're rearranging deck chairs on the titanic. like, why bother building a life, or a career, or even trying to connect with people when the foundation we're all standing on is literally collapsing? it feels so pointless to keep pushing forward when the end is inevitable.",
