      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That feeling of futility is a very rational response to the overwhelming scope of the problems we face. While major crises are massive, the human experience is also defined by moments of beauty, connection, and small victories that exist *within* the present. Choosing to build something meaningful, even if it's temporary, is a powerful assertion of value against the backdrop of chaos. Perhaps the point isn't to save the entire world, but to make the time we have here as meaningful as possible for ourselves and those around us.",
      "source": "target",
