    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it just feels like i'm being told to enjoy a beautiful sunset while the house is burning down around me. it’s hard to find meaning in \"temporary\" things when the weight of the inevitable is so heavy. honestly, it sometimes feels like the most logical thing to do is just... not be here for it. to just opt out before the chaos becomes too much. does that even make sense? like, if the future is a lost cause, isn't it just more merciful to leave early?",
